latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Heyy, came up with this random idea cause I was literally sick of getting dms and opportunities which were either barter where you're not even allowed to actually use the product. This is the reality. These days, influencers promote products without even using them. And for a matter of fact, influencers gained popularity only because we couldn't trust celebrities and cricketers promoting brands and products. Influenver should be one of us and should portray the reality than just being another sheep in the heard. 

Today, I wish to break the sad reality as most of the influencers do it because they wish to earn extra money. It is what it is they say. And tbh I have done collabs too though I have always made sure I use the product enough to share my experience. But again the truth remains. 

It was a v short fun sketch I made in just 5 mins. It might not be v creatively made due to time constraints but I still hope you'll watch it. Thank you!

#thewholetruthsayers #reality #influencer #influencers #lifestyleinfluencer #callingout

latestIgtvVideos.title: To Stars, We're Beautiful ❤
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I once made this video for my YouTube and I always wanted to post this one on Instagram too. This video is very close to my heart as it expressed something that we already know but need to be reminded about. 

I have always felt comfortable in my skin, my body but there are a lot of people out there who are struggling to accept themselves the way they are. I am not saying that just accept yourself cause you're beautiful.  I know its a process, its a journey that takes place at its own pace. I'm just here to remind you that you're on the right path. You're worthy and you'll be able to accept yourself sooner or later. I'm just here to cheer you up through a video message. Please believe in yourself.❤

latestIgtvVideos.caption:

I know their families are also suffering from this mental stress and doubt of whether they will be able to educate their children or not. 
What you and I can do is sacrifice a lil bit from our pockets becahse We are so priveleged and lucky that we get to do this. Please help me and join to help raise funds for these children. 
Please help me in this journey and I will make sure that every donation that you'll make will be very transparent. Every name of the donor and the amount will be displayed and you'll get the confirmation receipt as well. 

Thank you so please do help me by clicking the link in my bio. Your support will make tomorrow's future. ❤️❤️

latestPosts.caption:
You’ve probably seen me show up at events, talk about mental health, advocate for it over and over again, and be out there doing a million things.
But here I am… writing this down in pyjamas, on my bed, physically sick, exhausted, burnt out and maybe even anxious (Exam season), with not being able to eat things properly. 

Yes, this has been happening lately..

I don’t even know what exactly happened these past few weeks, but I didn’t feel like myself.
Like my spark had gone.
I felt alone. With thoughts like no one really cares. 
And the worst part? I didn’t even feel like working on TDP (Which, if you know me, is the thing that lights me up. It’s my passion. My work. One of my identities)

Was it emotional exhaustion from the MPhil training? (It’s been intense. And I literally did my research on the mental well-being of MHPs. So I should have known, right? But maybe I forgot it would feel like this.)
Was it burnout from holding so many roles and responsibilities? (But again, I signed up for them, didn’t I?) Or maybe just plain anxiety? About the future, about my goals, about me? 

It’s been so long, managing everything, encouraging others, leading a team, working on deadlines, handling cases, and doing it all in this everyday loop.
And in all of that, I stopped hanging out with friends.
Stopped talking to people.
Stopped feeling like anyone could really add anything… because deep down I felt like nothing could be done about it. I didn't and still honestly don't feel like telling this to my people cause it doesn't really matter?

And you know what? While feeling and experiencing all of this..It hit me—
I’ve always been someone who believes in being vulnerable. In embracing emotions fully. In expressing them. Because that’s how we connect, right? That’s how we belong.

And because we are so used to holding spaces for others, we sometimes forget the chaos. I forgot to take care of myself. And that made me feel like I was slowly losing parts of who I am.

(Also, hello to cognitive distortions. Of course I started catastrophizing. Felt like nobody would care about me, that everything’s falling apart. But it wasn’t true, it isn't true). 

(Contd in comments)
